title: Untitled
content:
-- Twitch Chat Simulator

local monitor = peripheral.wrap("left") -- Replace "right" with the side where your monitor is
monitor.clear()
monitor.setTextScale(0.5)
monitor.setCursorPos(1, 1)

-- Sample data
local usernames = {"User1", "GamerGirl", "NoobMaster69", "ProPlayer", "ChatBot"}
local messages = {
    "Hello everyone!",
    "GG!",
    "What a play!",
    "Can someone help me?",
    "Nice stream!",
    "LUL",
    "PogChamp",
    "Kappa",
    "This game is awesome!"
}
local emotes = {"Kappa", "PogChamp", "LUL", "FeelsBadMan", "BibleThump", "CoolCat"}

-- Random generators
function getRandomUsername()
    return usernames[math.random(#usernames)]
end

function getRandomMessage()
    local message = messages[math.random(#messages)]
    -- Insert emote randomly in message
    if math.random() < 0.3 then -- 30% chance to add an emote
        local emote = emotes[math.random(#emotes)]
        message = message .. " " .. emote
    end
    return message
end

function generateChatLine()
    local username = getRandomUsername()
    local message = getRandomMessage()
    return username .. ": " .. message
end

-- Main loop
while true do
    local chatLine = generateChatLine()
    local x, y = monitor.getCursorPos()
    local w, h = monitor.getSize()
    
    if y > h then
        monitor.clear()
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, 1)
        y = 1
    end
    
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, y)
    monitor.write(chatLine)
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, y + 1)
    
    -- Sleep for a bit before generating next line
    os.sleep(1)
end
